{{Other uses|Thomas Jacobsen (disambiguation){{!}}Thomas Jacobsen}} '''Thomas Jakobsen''' is a [[mathematician]], [[cryptographer]], and [[computer programmer]], formerly an assistant professor at the [[Technical University of Denmark]] (DTU) and head of research and development at [[IO Interactive]]. His notable work includes designing the [[physics engine]] and 3-D pathfinder algorithms for ''[[Hitman: Codename 47]]'', and the [[cryptanalysis]] of a number of [[block cipher]]s.
Jakobsen earned an [[M.Sc.]] in engineering and [[Ph.D.]] in mathematics, both from DTU.
